description:
Branch: feat/datetimepicker-brand-combined
Base: release/v1.4.0 (cut AFTER Fix #1 c1u7yn8g squash-merges — touches same GiftCardActions.tsx file)
Order: 3 of 3 (LAST — depends on Fix #1)

Surgical scope: replace native <input type="datetime-local"> at two callsites in GiftCardActions.tsx with a new brand <DateTimePicker> that composes existing <DatePicker> + <TimePicker>.

Component contract (locked per SESSION_BOOT):
```ts
type DateTimePickerProps = {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  label: string;
  value: string;        // "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm" (datetime-local shape)
  onChange: (value: string) => void;
  error?: string;
  required?: boolean;
  disabled?: boolean;
  min?: string;
  max?: string;
};
```

File map:
- src/components/Form/DateTimePicker/DateTimePicker.tsx — NEW. Splits value → renders <DatePicker> + <TimePicker> side-by-side (stacked on mobile via `flex-col sm:flex-row`); recombines on change.
- src/components/Form/DateTimePicker/DateTimePicker.test.tsx — NEW. Tests:
  - Split→recombine ISO-local roundtrip preserves value byte-for-byte
  - Change in either child emits combined value to parent
  - min/max delegate to DatePicker (date-only portion)
- src/app/my-gifts/GiftCardActions.tsx — TWO callsites updated:
  - Edit-recipient drawer (around line 195-205): replace native input with <DateTimePicker>
  - FlipToScheduledControl (around line ~391): same replacement
- (No changes to DatePicker.tsx or TimePicker.tsx — pure composition)

Reuse target: src/components/IntakeForm/renderField.tsx:96,119 already composes DatePicker + TimePicker separately for booking intake. <DateTimePicker> is the encapsulated reuse of that pattern.

Verification:
- pnpm typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm build
- Real-Chromium smoke at 375px (per R4 in plan PRD): open edit-recipient drawer, open both pickers, verify no popover stacking regression after PR #213's recent picker arc.
- Visual parity check vs booking intake page (same DatePicker + TimePicker components, should look consistent).

Constraints:
- No changes to <DatePicker> or <TimePicker> internals
- No native datetime-local input left in GiftCardActions.tsx (anti-criterion ISC-A-2)
- Composition only — no re-implementation of date/time logic

